CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F372A1782919121
OL,3,CHow will the next heatwave be
OL,4,Cdifferent from the last one?
OL,6,FAt this stage, it's looking close to
OL,7,F30C across parts of the south and
OL,8,Fsouth east, potentially hotter.
OL,10,FInto next week, temperatures will rise
OL,11,Fa few degrees, generally around 30-33C
OL,12,Fin the hottest spots.
OL,14,FThis is more of an example of "home-
OL,15,Fgrown heat" - day-on-day heating from
OL,16,Fstrong July sunshine, rather than the
OL,17,Finfluence of intense heat from the
OL,18,Fcontinent.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G4/10
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
