PN,37208
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F372A1782919121
OL,3,CHow will the next heatwave be
OL,4,Cdifferent from the last one?
OL,6,FWe will see a combination of "home-
OL,7,Fgrown" summer heat and heat generated
OL,8,Ffrom the near continent as July
OL,9,Funfolds.
OL,11,FEpisodes of above-average temperatures
OL,12,Fwill be broken by fresher days, such
OL,13,Fas this week.
OL,15,FNorthern and north-western areas are
OL,16,Fless likely to be influenced by this
OL,17,Fsoutherly sourced heat.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G8/10
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,373,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37209
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F372A1782919121
OL,3,CHow will the next heatwave be
OL,4,Cdifferent from the last one?
OL,6,FThere's also a chance that low
OL,7,Fpressures from the mid-Atlantic will
OL,8,Fbring cooler air and more modest
OL,9,Ftemperatures.
OL,11,FThis ties in with the three-month Met
OL,12,FOffice seasonal forecast issued
OL,13,Fearlier this week.
OL,15,FThe stats indicate we're twice as
OL,16,Flikely to see hotter-than-average
OL,17,Fconditions and an increased chance of
OL,18,Ffurther heatwaves.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G9/10
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
